{
  "text": "Early EEG is a reliable predictor of outcome in hypoxic induced encephalopathy. A normal or mildly abnormal EEG results within six hours after birth were associated with normal neurodevelopmental outcomes at two years. [CITATION_1] An abnormal EEG pattern of suppression-burst or continuous low voltage within three to eight hours of life was associated with a poor outcome, whereas a normal EEG almost invariably indicated a good outcome in term infants.",
